E4Plus1.uk.description: The Wettest Stories Ever Told: When the Simpsons' plans for a meal at The Frying Dutchman are ruined, they try to salvage the night by telling three tales of disaster at sea. (S17 Ep18/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Girls Just Want to Have Sums: When Principal Skinner gets cancelled for sexism, the school gets a new principal who mollycoddles the girls. So Lisa disguises herself as a boy. (S17 Ep19/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Father Knows Worst: Marge finds a sauna in the basement but doesn't tell anyone about it. Homer decides to get more involved in the children's education. (S20 Ep18/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Covercraft: Homer forms a band with four other dads, but their modest early success is soon overwhelmed by the breakout potential of lead singer Apu. (S26 Ep8/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Luxury car seller Sam likes his women 'fast and topless'. Is ex-teacher MJ open to Sam's kinky sex desires? Black belt Keira meets former footballer Max. (S16 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Monster Hunter
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2020) Paul WS Anderson's sci-fi action starring Milla Jovovich, based on the game of the same name. A US Army Ranger must fight her way out of a parallel world full of monsters.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction
E4Plus1.uk.description: Twitch streamer Fi gets likes all day but struggles to make a connection in real life. Bondage-lover Elle is after a sophisticated silver fox who's dirty in the bedroom. (S10 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction's Best Naughty...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Bits: We celebrate our celibate daters and the pickers who entered the studio with their virginity very much intact, ready for a televisual awakening like no other.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: This time on Gogglebox, The Yorkshire Vet, Britain's Got Talent, Dynamo: Beyond Belief, The Nest, and BBC News on Boris Johnson and Donald Trump. (S15 Ep9) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Below Deck Sailing Yacht
E4Plus1.uk.description: An Eye for Decline: It's all hands on deck to prevent a nautical crisis in the middle of the night. And is the yacht life too much for one crew member? (S5 Ep8/16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Simpson Christmas Stories: Homer shares his version of Jesus's birth, Grampa tells a Yuletide war story, and Springfield prepares for Christmas. (S17 Ep9/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Lake Life: Jay makes the family take their holiday on a houseboat to create memories that will last long after he's gone. And Mitchell runs into an old flame. (S9 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Long Goodbye: Phil and Claire realise that Alex is more self-sufficient in college than they thought. Manny is determined to avoid a tearful goodbye when he moves to college. (S9 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Stolen Sneakers: When Malcolm is robbed and won't reveal the culprit, Calvin and Dave team up to crack the case of the missing sneakers. (S1 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Fundraiser: Tina tries to help Gemma with her first fundraiser as school principal. Dave helps Calvin try to win a silent-auction prize. (S1 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to Fight Night: Calvin reluctantly invites Dave to join his guys' night at home with Malcolm and Marty. Gemma and Tina take a girls' trip to Vegas. (S1 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Dating Game: Barry convinces Geoff to go on The Dating Game to help him move on from Erica. And Murray's big surprise for Beverly backfires. (S8 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Daddy Daughter Day 2: Murray jumps in to help Erica get over her breakup with Geoff. Adam cooks up a senior prank to cement his legacy at William Penn. (S8 Ep19)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Poker Night: With Geoff away on spring break, Lainey heads to Hollywood to see her best friend. Adam is invited to join the cool kids' poker night. (S8 Ep20)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: Alligator Schwartz: Erica returns from spring break determined to find out where she stands with Geoff. Adam's plan to get Dave Kim a date for prom backfires. (S8 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Proposal: Geoff's plan to surprise Erica with a marriage proposal unleashes a classic romcom mix-up. (S8 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Wedding March 4: Something Old...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Something New: (2018) Romance. Mick and Olivia are still trying to get some time alone. But after they arrange the perfect wedding, the bride starts to have second thoughts. Argh!

E4Plus1.uk.title: Made in Chelsea
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series: Jazz is caught between Demi and Jules. Livvy cools things off with Kit... before Chuggs swoops in! And will Tabitha obey Sophie's orders not to see Arman again?! (S30 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hotel Transylvania 2
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2015) Animated family comedy sequel. Mavis (Selena Gomez) and Johnny (Andy Samberg) leave baby Dennis with 'Vampa' Dracula (Adam Sandler), who organises a monster boot camp.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Friendship Turbulence: In an attempt to improve their strained friendship, Howard invites Sheldon to visit NASA with him. Penny is upset when her car breaks down. (S7 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Mommy Observation: Sheldon pays a surprise visit to his mother in Houston and is forced to confront a new reality. Raj throws a murder mystery-themed dinner party. (S7 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Indecision Amalgamation: Raj has a dating dilemma. Penny can't decide whether to accept a role in a terrible film. Sheldon chooses between two gaming systems. (S7 Ep19)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Relationship Diremption: Sheldon wonders whether he's wasting his time with his study of string theory. Raj and Emily go on a double date with Howard and Bernadette. (S7 Ep20)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Anything Can Happen Recurrence: Penny and Leonard distract Sheldon from his career problems by reinstating Anything Can Happen Thursday. Raj asks for Howard's advice. (S7 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Proton Transmogrification: Sheldon struggles to process his feelings of grief when his idol Professor Proton passes away. The gang gather to celebrate Star Wars Day. (S7 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Gorilla Dissolution: Penny re-evaluates her life, including taking a big step with Leonard, while Howard and Bernadette struggle to look after Mrs Wolowitz. (S7 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Status Quo Combustion: With potential changes affecting different aspects of his personal and professional life, Sheldon is forced to confront an uncertain future. (S7 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Locomotion Interruption: Leonard and Amy take an impromptu road trip to Arizona to pick up Sheldon when his epic railway journey ends in chaos. Penny has an interview. (S8 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Junior Professor Solution: When Sheldon has to teach a course at the university, Howard enrols in his class. Tension brews between Penny and Bernadette. (S8 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly: A volunteer inspires Bart to become a better person. Lisa writes an essay about what Springfield will be like in 50 years' time. (S20 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Father Knows Worst: Marge finds a sauna in the basement but doesn't tell anyone about it. Homer decides to get more involved in the children's education. (S20 Ep18/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: We're on the Road to D'oh-where: Homer misses a Moe's Tavern trip to Las Vegas when he has to drive Bart to juvenile delinquent camp. (S17 Ep11/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Seemingly Never-Ending Story: When Homer and Lisa get trapped in a cave, she tells him about a day she spent with Mr Burns after a goat chased her into his mansion. (S17 Ep13/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bangalore: Mr Burns outsources the plant to India and puts Homer in charge of training the workforce. Patty and Selma kidnap a celebrity. (S17 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Wettest Stories Ever Told: When the Simpsons' plans for a meal at The Frying Dutchman are ruined, they try to salvage the night by telling three tales of disaster at sea. (S17 Ep18/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Celebrity favourites and some of Britain's best-loved LGBTQ+ personalities hit the sofa for a Pride anniversary special, including Rylan, Clare Balding, Scott Mills and Paul Sinha. (S4 Ep4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Goggleboxers watch Wheel of Fortune, Trigger Point, Love Is Blind, Boarders, Michael McIntyre's Big Show and more. (S23 Ep2)

Film4.uk.title: The Green Mile
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Drama with Tom Hanks and Michael Clarke Duncan. Strange events occur when a man convicted of raping and murdering two young girls arrives on death row in a Louisiana prison.

Film4.uk.title: The Last King of Scotland
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Oscar and BAFTA-winning Forest Whitaker stars as Idi Amin - the murderous Ugandan dictator, who mesmerises a young Scottish doctor, played by James McAvoy.

Film4.uk.title: Saraband for Dead Lovers
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Historical drama starring Joan Greenwood and Stewart Granger. Princess Dorothea marries the future king of England. But then she meets a Swedish count...

Film4.uk.title: Storm over the Nile
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Drama. Anthony Steel stars as a disgraced soldier who, during the British army's 1898 campaign in Sudan, goes way beyond the call of duty to prove his courage. With Laurence Harvey.

Film4.uk.title: The Wackiest Ship in the Army
Film4.uk.description: (1961) World War II comedy starring Jack Lemmon. A luckless naval lieutenant is duped into commanding a dangerous mission into enemy territory during the Battle of the Bismarck Sea.

Film4.uk.title: Hangman's Knot
Film4.uk.description: (1952) Civil War-era Western. A unit of Confederate soldiers attack a Union troop to steal gold. Learning that the war is over, they must finish the mission in disguise.

Film4.uk.title: Gemini Man
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Will Smith stars in Ang Lee's action-thriller as both an over-the-hill hitman and the young clone of himself sent to take him out. With Clive Owen.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance star in Steven Spielberg's Cold War spy drama. After gaining notoriety for defending a Soviet spy, a US lawyer then tries to free a CIA pilot.

Film4.uk.title: Mean Streets
Film4.uk.description: (1973) Scorsese's classic crime drama about the ordinary lives of mafiosi - the boredom, casual violence and shattered dreams - in Little Italy, with Harvey Keitel and Robert De Niro.

Film4.uk.title: The Double
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Dark psychological thriller. Jesse Eisenberg stars as a timid man whose drab existence takes a turn for the worse with the arrival of a new colleague at work. With Chris Morris.

Film4.uk.title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
Film4.uk.description: (1949) This dark comedy from Ealing studios sees Alec Guinness take on the roles of eight characters, all the noble victims of a vengeance-seeking relative, played by Dennis Price.

Film4.uk.title: San Demetrio, London
Film4.uk.description: (1943) Fact-based drama about a group of Merchant Navy sailors who brave fire and the ocean to save the San Demetrio oil tanker after it's almost destroyed by a German cruiser.

Film4.uk.title: Man in the Saddle
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Western. Randolph Scott stars as a rancher who's the target of unwelcome harassment by his richer and more powerful neighbour. With Alexander Knox, Joan Leslie and Ellen Drew.

Film4.uk.title: The Iron Petticoat
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Comedy with Katharine Hepburn and Bob Hope. A Russian captain defects to London, falls for the charms of Major Lockwood, and tries to convince him of the beauty of communism.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: Anna

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Building the Canals: Fred Dibnah explores the work of the builders and engineers responsible for the waterways of Britain, visiting the Leeds-Liverpool and Bridgewater canals. S1 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Building of Britain
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Victorian Splendour: Fred Dibnah explores his passion for 19th-century buildings, concentrating on Eastnor Castle in Herefordshire and St Giles's Church in Cheadle. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Industrial Landscape: Fred Dibnah traces the development of steam power from the earliest experiments in the ancient world to the modern nuclear power station. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's World of Steam, Steel & Stone
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Backstreet Mechanic: A look at Fred Dibnah's back garden, which housed one of the best examples of a steam-powered engineering workshop in the country. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Made in Britain
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Mechanics and Riveters: Astounding bits of engineering. Fred stops off at Andy Thornton's, a company that makes ornate carvings, and moves on to Worsborough to make hot forge rivets. Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Fred Dibnah's Made in Britain
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Pattern Making: Engineering travels with the great man. Leaving his engine to be fixed, Fred visits David Ragsdale, a skilled pattern maker who just happens to own six steam engines. Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: VW Golf Cabriolet: Derek and Paul are off to Leeds on a rare father and son road trip to pick up a VW Cabriolet and a Lotus Elite. S8 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Jaguar Challenger XJ6: A beautiful looking sports car has been fooling the punters and intriguing Derek. It's a Challenger E-Type - a fibreglass replica created from an E-Type mould. S8 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Paul Smith Mini / TY80: The team send their Paul Smith Mini in for a bit of designer tailoring by the team at Mini Sport. S7 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: 1961 Morris Minor 1000: Paul and Jack head to Staffordshire to pick up five vehicles from collector Rob's colossal barn, including a Mini and a Morris Minor. S8 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Merc G-Wagon/Opel Manta: There's an unlikely arrival at the North Yorkshire car auction - an Argentinian Army Mercedes G wagon that saw action in the Falklands War. S5 Ep11
